Plot was difficult to get to due to thick Psicat. Approx. 4 hours on first navigation. In future, may be possible to follow old TR19 flagging or white/blue dot flagging trail (eventually intersects with plot). For setup/1st reading, a direct trail was established and then flagging removed on last day to prevent confusion with TR 19 flagging. 2015 start X267621 Y2155163 +/-6m. 2010 end X267571 2155180 +/-3m. 2021 update: We camped at north camp and hiked to the plot. Right before we got to the plot, we came across an empty camp. We found T2 end post, ran transect backwards to T2 start (assigned 299 azimuth), but T2 start post was offset to the right by 5m so post was adjusted and new bearings were taken as shown on map. There was also a large fallen sicat in Q1 across T2 and T4. JG and KA decided if there is no past existing tree like growth, only living growth is vertical, fallen tree is old enough for small tree growth (>1cm). New downed tree is new substrate

Plot_Notes: [Updated: 2021] - 2015 data sheets often have cycden or cycpar w/ the absence of deppet, while 2021 crew confirmed DEPPET as present in plots/transects. 2021 crew found 28 more species present in plot then what was seen in 2015.  Plot updated by Emazengia, 8/31/2021. We found T2s + T2e and ran it. We were short a meter, so we moved it to keep consistency so there will be no future offset. There is slope in Q3 and Q4 parallel to T5, to the tape hovers in the air insead of running over  the ground.  RM TR3 runs through plot. T1-T4: Flag on small METPOL, tags directly below. T2-T4: Start point stake below several fallen CIBGLA. T3-T4: Open SETPAL, EHRSTI, JAPHAW field beyond T3 start. T2-T6: Flag in x2 large CIBGLA's near open SETPAL. T1-T6: CIBGLA. T3-T6: Under woody debris. 2010 coordinates start X265300 Y2159672, end X265302 Y2159628.

Plot_Notes: 2022: Crew used 161 azimuth and will continue to do so in future cycles. 2016: Found plot set up and GPS coordinates match back azimuth so changed to 161 from originally recorded as 341. Need to check next time. 2011 GPS coords: UTM start X247728 Y2159409 Center X247735 Y2159388 End X247745 Y2159363 no errors recorded. Trimble GEOXT start (X) 247726.01 (Y) 2159405.12 (error) 0.81m (PDOP) 2.59; end (X) 247743.37 (Y) 2159360.00 (error) 0.53m (PDOP) 2.5; center (X) 247735.04 (Y) 2159383.91 (error) 0.60m (PDOP) 2.00. Endpost offset 80cm beyond end of TR 2 (50m). Note T2 slope listed as -7 in 2011 which is very different from 5 recorded in 2016. Blue flagging tied at eye level in ohia tree. Outside plot beyond end post. Left all 9 pin flags; in shallow soil. 2022: 2011 plot was done with 341 azimuth; however, it was created following the back azimuth, so actual azimuth is 161. Only marked witness trees when vegetation was available. Plot open and easy to set up. Because of issue with azimuth, 2011 shrub belt was read on T3 using 161 azimuth. In cycle 2, plot set up assuming it was flipped because of the azimuth and shrub belt read on T1. In cycle 3, changed the azimuth and read shrub belt on T3.
QA_notes: See note about changing azimuth and T1 vs T3 for shrubbelt. Everything should line up correctly now and in future.

Plot_Notes: Use alternate 4 to replace R32, all data taken as R32, azimuth used for A4. Some tree ferns look like C. menziesii except no stiff, straight, dark brown hairs on stipe. These were called C. chamissoi, but do not exactly match characteristics of C. chamissoi either. (ie, pinnae sinuses not cut 7/8 or more to costa, no tan arachnoid hairs on abaxial surface segment).  For Understory Cover data, ELA GALA (Elaphoglossum group alatum) entered as ELAFAU as a default, but not keyed between other group alatum Elaphoglossum.
